      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/y/d9b06d/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2022-05-05T20:33:33.560Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I love the slope feature for most interval workouts.  However, there are times (i.e, when traveling) when I may want to execute the workout from my Garmin so I can use my phone for other things, but of course the standard workout formats don\u2019t specify slope changes.  Perhaps a workaround would be to export the workout as a course (GPX or FIT - not sure which would work best) that could then be replicated from another device/app.  Would this work?</p>",
